@startuml AeroGrid_Architecture
title AeroGrid — Real-Time Turbine Telemetry & Anomaly Detection Pipeline

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 13
skinparam roundCorner 14
skinparam ArrowColor #5D6D7E
skinparam ArrowFontColor #5D6D7E
skinparam rectangleBorderColor #34495E
skinparam rectangleFontColor #1B2631
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FBFCFC
skinparam noteBorderColor #AEB6BF
skinparam noteFontColor #566573
left to right direction

rectangle "**Turbine Fleet**\nIoT sensors (10 -> 100s)" as sensors #EBF5FB
rectangle "**IoT Ingestion Gateway**\n//AWS IoT Core / MQTT//" as gateway #EBF5FB
rectangle "**Message Queue / Pub-Sub**\n//Apache Kafka / AWS Kinesis//" as queue #FEF9E7
rectangle "**Stream Processor**\n//Flink / Kinesis Analytics / AWS Lambda//\n(containerised anomaly logic)" as proc #E9F7EF
rectangle "**Hot Store**\n//Time-Series DB: Timestream / InfluxDB//" as hot #FDEDEC
rectangle "**Cold Store / Data Lake**\n//Amazon S3//" as cold #FDEDEC
rectangle "**Dashboard**\n//Grafana//" as dash #F4ECF7
rectangle "**Alerting**\n//SNS / PagerDuty//" as alert #F4ECF7
actor "Engineering /\nOps Team" as ops

sensors --> gateway : telemetry stream
gateway --> queue   : publish
queue   --> proc    : consume (real time)
queue   --> cold    : raw archive
proc    --> hot     : metrics + anomaly flags
proc    --> alert   : on anomaly
hot     --> dash    : query
dash    --> ops     : monitor
alert   --> ops     : notify

note bottom of queue
  Buffers bursts & decouples fast producers
  from slower / fragile consumers.
  Partitioned + replicated across zones
  => **no single point of failure**.
end note
note bottom of proc
  Applies rules in real time over a sliding window:
  mean temp > 85.0 C  **OR**  vibration spike > 15.0 mm/s.
  Scales horizontally; can restart without data loss
  (unprocessed events stay safe in the queue).
end note
note bottom of cold
  Hot  = recent, fast, for live dashboards.
  Cold = cheap, full history, for audit / ML.
end note
@enduml